  "decision_conditions": [
    "&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;line-height: normal;&quot;&gt;The proposed rear roof dormer and outrigger dormer, by reason of their excessive cumulative size, bulk, scale and massing would result in an overly dominant, incongruous, bulky and visually obtrusive form of development, which would be at odds with the prevailing visual character of both the host property and wider area. The proposal is therefore contrary to the high quality design aspirations of the National Planning Policy Framework (2023), Policy D3.D1 and D3.D11 of The London Plan (2021), Core Policy CS1.B of the Harrow Core Strategy (2012), Policy DM1 of the Harrow Development Management Policies Local Plan (2013) and the adopted Supplementary Planning Document: Residential Design Guide (2010).&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;"
